<chapter xml:id="db_pil_wui_jobActivitiesView" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    version="5.1" xml:lang="en-US">
    <title>Handling Job Activities</title>
    <para>The <guilabel>Job Activities</guilabel> view displays the activities for all jobs, which were imported and processed by <productname>&dbpi;</productname>. The following actions are supported for the <guilabel>Job Activities</guilabel> view:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="display_jobActivities"/></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="display_jobActivity_details"/></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="filter_jobActivities"/></para>
        </listitem>

    </itemizedlist>
    <sect1 xml:id="display_jobActivities"><?dbhtml filename="SearchJobActivitiesView.html" ?><title>Listing Job Activities</title>
        <para>You can display an overview of the activities for the imported and processed jobs in the <guilabel>Jobs Activities</guilabel> view.</para>
        <mediaobject><alt>Screenshot Job Activities view</alt><imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_JobActivitiesViewGen.png" width="15cm" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>The overview table displays the following information for each process by default:</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>ID</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The automatically generated unique identifier of the job activity (sequential number).</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Process</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The process to which the job, and therefore the job activity, is assigned.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Source job</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Unique identifier of the source job (e.g. for merge and split actions).</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Job</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Unique identifier of the job to which the job activity is related.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Action</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Action name.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Created</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Timestamp (date and time) of the moment when the action was saved.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Context</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Unique context ID (UUID).</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="display_jobActivity_details">
        <title>Listing Job Activity Details</title>
        <para>You can display the details for a specific job activity in the details pane. The details pane contains the same scope of information as the overview table.</para>
        <mediaobject><alt>Details Pane</alt><imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_JobActivitiesViewDetails.png" align="left"
                    width="15cm" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="filter_jobs">
        <title>Filtering Job Activities</title>
        <para>Use this action to filter the overview of available job activities based on the available columns.</para>
        <para>Proceed as follows to filter the existing job activities and thus reduce the number of displayed job activities.</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Switch to the <guilabel>Job Activities</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the view, click <guibutton>Filter</guibutton>.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>You can filter the existing job activities by ID (simple filter) or by other parameters (for more information about filter criteria, see <xref linkend="db_pil_wui_filterSettings"/>).</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
